sect3.para:
The Ajax handler is the server side component to be implemented
      for managing Ajax events. This is the interface of an Ajax handler,
      followed by a description of its methods:

sect3.programlisting:
public interface AjaxHandler { 

public boolean supports(AjaxEvent event); 

public AjaxResponse handle(AjaxEvent event); 
}

listitem.para:
public boolean supports(AjaxEvent event)
          : Check if this handler supports (can handle)
          the given, generic, AjaxEvent

sect3.programlisting:
public interface AjaxAction { 

public String execute(); 

}

public interface Component { 

public String render(); 

}

public interface AjaxResponse { 

public void addAction(AjaxAction action); 

public String getResponse(); 
}

listitem.para:
public void addAction(AjaxAction action)
          : This method is used for adding actions that will be executed and
          whose result will be sent to the client.

sect4.programlisting:
